            <title>[SOLR-1225] improve LukeRequestHandler docCount calculation</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-1225</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently the LukeRequestHandler is calling: &lt;br/&gt;
 int docCount = searcher.numDocs( q, matchAllDocs ); &lt;br/&gt;
followed by:&lt;br/&gt;
 DocList ds = searcher.getDocList( q, (Query)null, (Sort)null, 0, 1 );&lt;br/&gt;
to get the doc count (and then the first doc returned)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This can be replaced with:&lt;br/&gt;
 TopDocs top = searcher.search( q, 1 );&lt;/p&gt;</description>
